Sep 17 2009	Taxi Trouble	We stayed here for 4 nights at the start of September. The hotel is conveniently situated with hutons and restaurants nearby, Times Square shopping mall next door, 2 subway stations and a short walk to Tiananmen Square. Breakfast was included and supplied a continental breakfast alongside a japanese one. The hotel had a pool and gym with a few CV machines and a multigym in the corner. Rooms were clean and staff were polite. The only trouble we had was getting back to the hotel! A number of times we tried with taxi drivers showing them the location on a map and even giving them the hotel card with the address written in Chinese however they pretended they didn't understand or couldn't read. We were later told by a local tour guide that taxi drivers don't like the location in Xidan because of the busy road and area. By day 2 we gave up and used the subway.	
