Aug 15 2009 	Everything we could have needed or asked for...	We stayed at the Mercure whilst enjoying Beijing on our honeymoon last month. Absolutely and totally impressed with every aspect of the hotel and staff. We were upgraded as soon as they learned we were on our honeymoon, and the rooms were well furnished, spacious enough and welcoming. Oh, and the beds were the comfiest out of everywhere we went in China! I loved that there was a bath and a shower in the room as my feet needed a well deserved soak after every daily adventure. The swimming pool was also an absolute godsend, as were the jacuzzi and sauna rooms - hitting the streets of Beijing for hours and hours was hard work let me tell you! The breakfast was varied also, with both Chinese and Western options available. Compared to the other places we stayed in China, this hotel was a real favourite of ours and we would absolutely stay there again. I can't see how you would be disappointed. The nearest subway is 5 mins walking distance, and if you walk up the road past the hotel there are lots of shopping centres and places to eat, making the location even better. We also managed to get free internet access on the business floor - seems to only be available for free quite late on in the day about 8pm onwards - staff didn't seem mind, although during the day they stated the cost was equivalent of 10p per minute. Internet is scarce in Beijing so grab it while you can folks! Great city, great hotel, great service, great location...what more could you want? We spent ages looking at reviews and are so so glad we decided on this one!	
Jul 21 2009 	An Oasis - great location service interior; yet few points of improvement	I stayed at the Grand Mercure Beijing Xidan hotel in July 2009, together with my girlfriend for 2 nights. We choose this hotel because of its location, 4-star rating and the deal we were able to get through a website. The GMBX is indeed located favorably. To the north is subway station Xidan (5 min walk) and to the south is station Xuanwumen (5 min walk). The bus stop is near the mall, about 8 minutes to the north of the hotel. Both stations are part of a different line which was very convenient for us since we wanted to explore the city and its attractions. The Forbidden Palace and Tiananmen is on walking distance (approx 20 min, head north-east), a great walk in the evening when the temperature has cooled down a bit. When you're up for it, you could walk from Wangfujing to the hotel, via the Tiananmen (about 30 min in total) Furthermore, since Xidan is a well developed area, you will find some business, parks and luxury stores near the hotel. A grand shopping mall is just north of Xidan station (approx 10 min walk from the hotel). Also you will find a Starbucks in the food court / luxury clothing mall in the building just outside the hotel. Finally, next to the hotel is a post office which also sells postcards. From the first sight of the hotel, we noticed that it handles French hotel standards, which is a good thing. The hotel itself can be called beautiful, at least from the inside. The lobby is amazing with fine pottery and glasswork, as well as a big aquarium and a big lounge with bar. From the outside the hotel looks ok, but by far not as neat as the inside. Since we arrived early, the staff offered us free drinks in the lounge so we had a chance to experience the comfort as well as the service. Holding our bags for a few hours was not a problem at all which gave us the oppertunity to explore the city. Staff spoke English very well, yet if you need to talk to someone about more complicated issues, ask for the manager (he is French). Anyway, the room we had had a double bed, desk tv, airco, minibar etc. All the things you are used to from 3/4 star hotel are there, including tooth brushes, shower gel, shampoo, towels, bath robes etc. The room was spacious, something we did not expect, and we even had a lounge chair with foot rest. We found the room clean and with two complimentary (daily) bottles of water, the start of our stay was relaxed. What we didnt like however was the bathroom. The shower seems to be somewhat dated, as well as the toilet which almost fell apart. We expected something more for a 4-star hotel so if there is something the GMBX could improve, its defintily the bathroom. Yet, we did not mind it that much since it was still clean and all. The view from our big window was not impressive since we could see the inner rooftop of the hotel. This seemed to be a former swimming pool or terrace. Now weed is growing all over it. This is perhaps the poorest part and most disappointing of the hotel in terms of interior and exterior. Coming back to our hotel after a busy day, felt like returning at an oasis. Refreshing yourself with a beverage and washing away the filth of the streets in our room. Also, our nights were very quiet and comfortable. Unfortunately I did not have the time to explore the indoor swimming pool and fitness center, but according to reviews on this website, they are very nice.As mentioned before, the service is that of a 4-star hotel. Bell desk is quick and fast, reception booked a table for us at a famous Chinese restaurant and even provided us direction for the taxi driver (not that we didnt take one, but its nice to have it).Probably another thing we liked was the breakfast. Its a Sino-European breakfast: you can find rice and noodles, dumplings and some dim sum here, combined with eggs (scrambled, benedict, cooked), sausages (hot/cold), cheese, fruit, juices, excellent coffee, various types of bread etc. Breakfast was seriously a great start of the day, something you really need when exploring this city.All in all we thoroughly enjoyed our stay at the GMBX, dispite the few flaws.	
