May 29 2009 	Good 4-Star Choice	I stayed at the Grand Mercure as a result of the reviews on Tripadvisor.com. Overall I think this is a good choice for a 4-star hotel, but on the other hand it's nothing to rave about. I would consider staying here again if the price is right, but would easily consider other options as well. First of all, ignore the guy who said the rooms are better than many 5-star hotels. That is simply not true. The Grand Mercure's rooms are spacious and clean, but they are definitely of 4-star quality. My carpet was tolerable but could use a good cleaning. My bathroom sink had unsightly cracks and the toilet bowl wasn't exactly bleach white. The service was very friendly, but I also experienced some sub-par experiences such as: 1) It took them nearly 20 minutes to bring an iron and iron board 2) They forgot to replace my towels on one of the days 3) The cleaning lady insistently knocked on my door even when my &quot;Do Not Disturb&quot; sign was hung out (but she was very apologetic and friendly when that was pointed out to her).But like I said, for the price I paid (~RMB500 in May 2009) this hotel was a solid choice. The rooms were spacious, comfortable and clean enough for a 4-star hotel, and the location is excellent.	
